The paper discusses the design considerations for semi-automated tools for detecting biases in machine learning models. This involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
